'''''Star Wars Insider'' 86''' is the 86th issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]''. It began shipping to subscribers the week of [[February 13]], and shipped to newsstands on [[February 21]], [[2006]]. It saw the departure of editor-in-chief [[Brett Rector]] and associate art directory [[Gregory Harsh]], with [[Frank Parisi]] taking over as editor in the next issue.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]: News from Around the Galaxy"
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; [[The Last of the Jedi: Death on Naboo|Next of the Jedi]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; [[The Return of Tag & Bink: Special Edition|The Color of Funny]] {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; Chancellor's Holding Office and Senate Chamber: Clash of the Titans {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" &mdash; Four Arms Really Are Better Than Two {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; ''Star Wars'': Thirty Years and Not Halfway There! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Anchorhead Arcade]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars Galaxies: Trials of Obi-Wan|When Worlds Collide]] {{C|by [[Sid Shuman]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; Sideshow's 12-Inch Series Takes Center Stage {{C|by [[Frank Parisi]]}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; Spinning the Jedi Wheel of Fate {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 17 {{C|edited by [[Mary Franklin]]}}

===Features===
*"[[The Mandalorians: People and Culture]]" {{C|by [[Karen Traviss]]}}
*:<small>Forged by warfare. Defined by loyalty. Dominated by none. The origin, customs and way of life of the nomadic Mandalorian warriors have remained shrouded in mystery&mdash;until now.</small>
*"[[Posters of Episode VI: Return of the Jedi|Posters of Episode VI: ''Return of the Jedi'']]" {{C|by [[Pete Vilmur]]}}
*:<small>In the final installment of a three-part series, poster expert Pete Vilmur offers a glimpse at some of the unused concepts, advance artwork, and design variations from one of the most visually arresting image campaigns in the ''Star Wars'' saga.</small>
*"[[Unknown Soldier: The Story of General Grievous]]" {{C|by [[Abel G. Peña|Abel Peña]]}}
*:<small>He was known as Qymaen jai Sheelal until the Geonosians made him better than he was before. Better. Stronger. Faster. Under Count Dooku's training he became the leader of the droid army and one of the galaxy's most feared villains.</small>
*"[[A New Order (article)|A New Order]]" {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler|J. W. Rinzler]]}}
*:<small>By deepening our connections with pivotal characters and supplanting shock with suspense, the prequel trilogy will forever change the way we see, and feel about, the original trilogy. And you thought watching Luke and Leia kiss couldn't get any creepier.</small>
*"[[Yoda's Right Arm]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>From his subtle emotional nuances to his life and death battle against Darth Sidious, Yoda was ''Revenge of the Sith''{{'s}} shining digital start. Insider talks with ILM lead animator [[Jamy Wheless]], who was given the dream task of bringing the Master to life.</small>

